stylometry: You need to find the balance between how much inventory you need to have if you are worried about running out of product. If running out of product is important to your company than you want to make sure you have enough inventory to where you ensure this is likely to not occur. If you are not necessarily worried about running out of inventory than you do not have to look as closely at this decision of ordering. A company must consider how much it will cost them to hold the product versus the cost of ordering the product. If you are going to order the product a long time before it will be sold then you incurr holding costs that decrease your profit. Therefore you must order the perfect number at the perfect time to make sure that this does not happen to your company.
